{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For instance, Wu et al. [43] developed a framework integrating language-based planning with perception, enabling robots to adapt to user preferences with minimal prior interactions, particularly in user-centric applications.LLMs have also been applied to complex tasks such as multi-object rearrangement, where Ding et al.",
    "[44] demonstrated their utility in enhancing robotic motion planning and execution.",
    "Similarly, systems like CodeBotler [45] and LLM-Grounder [46] highlight the versatility of LLMs in programming service robots and improving 3D visual grounding, respectively.Further contributions include ProgPrompt [47] and Code as Policies [48], which adapt LLMs for generating dynamic task plans and policy codes from natural language instructions.",
    "These frameworks enable robots to exhibit agile and adaptable behaviors.",
    "However, challenges such as linguistic ambiguities and hallucinations in LLM outputs can hinder task execution."
  ],
